			<notes/>
			<notesNormalized/>
			<notesHtml/>
			<text>How is body temperature controlled?
Sensory receptors (thermoreceptors) respond to temperature (skin, brain, cardiovascular system)
Information relayed to hypothalamus (nervous system)
Thermoregulatory centre compares input to pre-determined set point (similar to a thermostat)
If sensory information indicates deviation from norm, (ie lower or higher) effectors are stimulated to activate heat generation, conservation or loss
Involve numerous body systems</text>
		</slide>
