			<notes/>
			<notesNormalized/>
			<notesHtml/>
			<text>How is heat generated within the body?
Environmental temperature
Ingestion of hot foods/fluids
Digestion
Cell metabolism (affected by catecholamines, thyroid hormones, growth hormone)
Skeletal muscle activity (including shivering)
Insulation (clothing, adipose tissue, piloerection)
Non-shivering thermogenesis (brown fat)</text>
		</slide>
		<slide index="9" title="How is heat lost from the body?" titleNormalized="how is heat lost from the body?" src="slide10.swf" size="1845" advanceOnTime="0" framesCount="1" hasEmbeddedFlashClip="0" hidden="0" level="0" advanceOnClick="1" thumbnailAssetId="">
